1
00:00:07,875 --> 00:00:12,833
[YOSHIO'S MOM gasps]

2
00:00:14,291 --> 00:00:15,666
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

3
00:00:22,083 --> 00:00:24,125
--[door rattles]
--[YOSHIO gasps]

4
00:00:27,416 --> 00:00:29,791
[YOSHIO'S DAD]
How do you feel?

5
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:31,125
[YOSHIO gasps]

6
00:00:31,208 --> 00:00:36,541
[YOSHIO'S MOM grunts]
Fine. Don't worry.

7
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,916
[YOSHIO gasps]

8
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:53,625
[YOSHIO grunts]

9
00:00:57,208 --> 00:00:58,708
My head.

10
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,041
[YOSHIO grunts]

11
00:01:07,916 --> 00:01:10,875
[grunts]

12
00:01:15,583 --> 00:01:18,500
[YOSHIO grunts]

13
00:01:18,583 --> 00:01:22,625
[YOSHIO'S MOM coughs]

14
00:01:22,708 --> 00:01:24,708
[YOSHIO whimpers]

15
00:01:28,416 --> 00:01:30,458
[footsteps]

16
00:01:30,541 --> 00:01:31,625
[YOSHIO'S DAD grunts]

17
00:01:31,708 --> 00:01:36,666
[grunts]

18
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:38,666
[YOSHIO'S DAD gasps]

19
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:40,833
[YOSHIO gasps]

20
00:01:46,208 --> 00:01:49,416
What is this feeling?

21
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:54,500
♪

22
00:03:25,958 --> 00:03:27,250
Take care of the rest.

23
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:28,541
Sir.

24
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:31,000
[HIDE] 'Bout to have a
grandbaby or something?

25
00:03:31,083 --> 00:03:31,875
Pardon?

26
00:03:31,958 --> 00:03:33,375
[HIDE]
The new room.

27
00:03:33,458 --> 00:03:36,833
Oh, no. There isn't
a baby on the way.

28
00:03:37,958 --> 00:03:41,166
Although. In the sense
that Master Hanasaki has

29
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:45,666
decided to take in new family,
it may mean the same thing.

30
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:49,916
[SUMIRE] With the
Stratophere Plane in place,

31
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,958
the New Tokyo World Fair is
almost ready! I'm so excited!

32
00:03:54,041 --> 00:03:55,958
And we won't have to
wait much longer!

33
00:03:56,041 --> 00:03:58,375
Indeed. But, there is
some trouble.

34
00:03:58,458 --> 00:04:01,916
Using the police as guards has
raised some public concern.

35
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,125
Huh? What's wrong
with the police?

36
00:04:04,208 --> 00:04:06,000
They've had several
blunders on their record

37
00:04:06,083 --> 00:04:08,833
over these past few months.
The most recent, of course,

38
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:10,583
being the attack on the
convicted murderer,

39
00:04:10,666 --> 00:04:14,333
Seiji Fukiya. People are
seeking reputable security,

40
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:16,500
so that they can enjoy
the event without fear.

41
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:17,833
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

42
00:04:17,916 --> 00:04:19,750
[FURUKAWA]
Sorry to interrupt you're rest.

43
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:22,583
I'm one of the renovators.

44
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:25,500
We need to check every room as
part of our initial examination

45
00:04:25,583 --> 00:04:26,666
of the property.

46
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:28,958
[KENSUKE]
Huh, really?

47
00:04:29,041 --> 00:04:31,500
I thought you were just
adding onto the place.

48
00:04:31,583 --> 00:04:34,166
[HIDE] Uh, actually, since the
house is so old, they asked us

49
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:36,083
to take a look around
and see if any repairs

50
00:04:36,166 --> 00:04:39,625
were needed beforehand.
You know how it goes.

51
00:04:39,708 --> 00:04:42,291
Just a quick look-see and
we'll be outta your hair.

52
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:48,250
[KENSUKE]
Hello, Hide.

53
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:50,750
[HIDE chuckles]

54
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:55,458
Whoa! Damn, Han. Your old
man must be rollin' in it.

55
00:04:57,041 --> 00:04:58,458
Ya think?

56
00:04:58,541 --> 00:05:01,375
If he wasn't filthy rich,
he'd never do this for his son.

57
00:05:01,458 --> 00:05:03,125
[FURUKAWA]
Uh, sorry. "Former" son.

58
00:05:03,208 --> 00:05:05,916
One that might never come
back in the first place.

59
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:12,083
What's up? Why go
through all this trouble?

60
00:05:12,166 --> 00:05:15,208
No choice. Someone
wouldn't answer my calls.

61
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:17,000
[KENSUKE]
Uh...

62
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:19,541
[HIDE] You missed out
on a good one yesterday.

63
00:05:19,625 --> 00:05:21,041
Huh?

64
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:23,500
[HIDE] There was this guy
smoking near the tracks, right?

65
00:05:23,583 --> 00:05:26,041
Stinkin' up the whole place.

66
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:28,125
He left the butt on the ground!

67
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:31,041
So, we gave him a taste
of his own medicine.

68
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:34,041
All over his house.

69
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:37,791
That'll do. Let's light'er up!

70
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,916
[HIDE]
Whoa! Not that much!

71
00:05:43,208 --> 00:05:46,041
Now. We're here to
officially invite you

72
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:48,375
to partake in the next mission.

73
00:05:48,458 --> 00:05:49,750
What?

74
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:52,791
Well, you see, we found this
awesome hole-in-the-wall

75
00:05:52,875 --> 00:05:55,750
restaurant, and someone's
making problems for it online.

76
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:58,083
Posting all kinds
of lies about them.

77
00:05:58,166 --> 00:05:59,208
See for yourself.

78
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:00,750
[KENSUKE]
Hm?

79
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:03,291
[FURUKAWA] This stuff is more
convincing than you'd think.

80
00:06:03,375 --> 00:06:05,458
[HIDE]
He even hid behind an alias.

81
00:06:05,541 --> 00:06:07,833
We can't let the
coward get away with it.

82
00:06:07,916 --> 00:06:10,125
Eye for an eye is the only way!

83
00:06:10,208 --> 00:06:12,708
Whaddya say, Han? Come with us.

84
00:06:12,791 --> 00:06:16,458
We'll serve justice and
have a blast doing it.

85
00:06:16,541 --> 00:06:17,916
[KENSUKE grunts]

86
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:22,000
No, Hide. I just can't be
one of your Hooligans, okay?

87
00:06:22,083 --> 00:06:23,208
Sorry.

88
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:26,083
Wait. You still upset
about the last time?

89
00:06:26,166 --> 00:06:28,250
Thought you'd be over that.

90
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:31,125
[KENSUKE] Nothing good
happens when I try to help.

91
00:06:31,208 --> 00:06:33,875
I don't know what to do.

92
00:06:33,958 --> 00:06:35,833
[HIDE]
Dude, come on.

93
00:06:35,916 --> 00:06:39,750
Everyone messes up at
some point. It's fine.

94
00:06:42,208 --> 00:06:43,916
Well, s'your loss.

95
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,458
[KENSUKE gasps]

96
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:47,708
[HIDE] Anyway, if ya get any
interesting missions, hit me up.

97
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:49,916
I'd be happy to tag along.

98
00:06:51,416 --> 00:06:53,750
[HIDE]
What? Was I being too cold?

99
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:56,708
No. Not really.

100
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:58,333
[HIDE]
It's not you, it's just...

101
00:06:58,416 --> 00:07:00,250
There's so many
things I wanna do.

102
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:02,875
Time's short. So, I gotta move!

103
00:07:02,958 --> 00:07:04,666
[gasps]

104
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:06,583
[HIDE]
Catch ya later, okay?

105
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,125
See ya.

106
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:12,750
[HIDE, FURUKAWA grunt]

107
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:14,833
[FURUKAWA]
You suck!

108
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:16,875
[FURUKAWA grunts]

109
00:07:16,958 --> 00:07:18,166
[HIDE grunts]

110
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:21,875
[door clatters]

111
00:07:21,958 --> 00:07:24,000
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

112
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:26,958
[AKASHI]
I'm sorry, sir.

113
00:07:27,041 --> 00:07:30,166
Did some people from the
renovation company come in here?

114
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,541
[KENSUKE]
Yeah.

115
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:35,250
They said there's
something they want to do.

116
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:36,791
[AKASHI]
And what would that be?

117
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:38,458
[KENSUKE grunts]

118
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:47,166
[phone buzzes]

119
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:51,416
[KATSUTA] Yes? Sunflowers?
Sure, give me a second.

120
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:54,625
I'm looking it
up now. Let's see.

121
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,416
Oh, you need seeds? No prob.

122
00:07:56,500 --> 00:08:00,000
Wow, helping out the flower
shop sounds thrilling.

123
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:02,041
[YAMANE]
I don't get how you do it.

124
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:06,125
Helping them and studying
for exams would kill me.

125
00:08:06,208 --> 00:08:07,750
[OHTOMO] And you've got
a tennis tournament soon,

126
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:09,083
if I'm not mistaken.

127
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:10,458
I like keeping busy.

128
00:08:10,541 --> 00:08:13,458
[OHTOMO] Ah. Has Inoue
dropped by recently?

129
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:15,333
No.

130
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:18,958
I guess he's taking care
of Kobayashi. He'll come soon.

131
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:21,083
Sure, if he doesn't
die of boredom

132
00:08:21,166 --> 00:08:23,416
now that the Boy
Detective's Club broke up.

133
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:26,333
I give him another week.

134
00:08:26,416 --> 00:08:31,666
So, is there anything we can do?
I hate just waiting around.

135
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:33,375
You really should
know better, Yamane.

136
00:08:33,458 --> 00:08:35,000
Whoa, whoa, whoa! What are you--

137
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:38,500
[OHTOMO] You shouldn't
worry about other people.

138
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:40,791
[yelps]

139
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,291
[YAMANE sighs]

140
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:46,916
Help yourself.
Lighten your own load.

141
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,583
Then you can help
others with their problems.

142
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:56,208
[INOUE] Kobayashi needs rest.
We'll talk here.

143
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:58,458
All right.
I'm being transferred.

144
00:08:58,541 --> 00:08:59,708
Really?

145
00:08:59,791 --> 00:09:02,208
Yeah, to Special Security.

146
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:03,666
[MIYANISHI grunts]

147
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,750
So you were forced
to take responsibility

148
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,791
for what happened to Fukiya.

149
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:13,375
Don't know what you mean.

150
00:09:13,458 --> 00:09:16,125
It's an honor to act as
security for the World Fair.

151
00:09:16,208 --> 00:09:18,250
I'd have volunteered.

152
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:20,875
[INOUE]
I'm sorry. This is our fault.

153
00:09:20,958 --> 00:09:22,625
None of that.

154
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:30,666
[NAKAMURA] By the way, Fukiya
was connected to Twenty-Faces.

155
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:32,166
[gasps]

156
00:09:32,250 --> 00:09:33,708
[NAKAMURA]
Apparently they made contact

157
00:09:33,791 --> 00:09:35,458
while he was still in prison.

158
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:39,166
After some "convincing" a few
other convicts confirmed it.

159
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:42,000
[INOUE]
Then he was behind everything?

160
00:09:42,083 --> 00:09:44,583
[NAKAMURA] That being the case,
it wasn't something we could

161
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:47,541
handle through
conventional means.

162
00:09:47,625 --> 00:09:49,666
Besides, if I kept
working at the pace

163
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:53,583
I was in general affairs,
I'd never see my boyfriend.

164
00:09:55,166 --> 00:09:56,583
[NAKAMURA]
I'm done with this.

165
00:09:56,666 --> 00:09:58,541
I just came by to say I
won't be around to clean up

166
00:09:58,625 --> 00:10:01,083
after you brats anymore.

167
00:10:01,166 --> 00:10:05,791
Kay? Go back to being
normal kids. It's for the best.

168
00:10:05,875 --> 00:10:10,041
I swear. I'll find a way to
bring you back, Detective!

169
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:14,708
[INOUE gasps]

170
00:10:14,791 --> 00:10:19,750
[pants]

171
00:10:27,708 --> 00:10:29,333
[YOSHIO grunts]

172
00:10:30,708 --> 00:10:32,125
Huh?

173
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:40,625
[YOSHIO gasps]

174
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:43,833
[NORO]
Hey, what's wrong?

175
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:44,916
[PIPPO hoots]

176
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,291
[YOSHIO gasps]

177
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:08,291
[YOSHIO grunts]

178
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:10,541
Ow.

179
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:14,625
[grunting continues]

180
00:11:14,708 --> 00:11:16,875
[elevator rumbles]

181
00:11:21,791 --> 00:11:23,166
[gasps]

182
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:37,541
[YOSHIO'S DAD] This is why
I never wanted a child!

183
00:11:37,625 --> 00:11:39,083
[YOSHIO whimpers]

184
00:11:39,166 --> 00:11:44,541
[YOSHIO'S MOM] That child...
is proof... that I was alive.

185
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:45,458
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

186
00:11:45,541 --> 00:11:48,291
[NORO]
Hey, Koba! Are you okay?

187
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:49,916
Say something!

188
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:50,958
[KENSUKE]
Kobayashi!

189
00:11:51,041 --> 00:11:53,250
[gasps]

190
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:55,375
[YOSHIO gasps]

191
00:11:59,666 --> 00:12:01,958
[grunts]

192
00:12:07,041 --> 00:12:09,291
[NORO]
So, what are you doing here?

193
00:12:09,375 --> 00:12:13,041
[KENSUKE] I was thinking
about what I wanna do.

194
00:12:13,125 --> 00:12:14,250
[NORO]
And?

195
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:17,500
What came to me was...

196
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:19,625
...to visit him.

197
00:12:19,708 --> 00:12:21,458
I see.

198
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:25,458
[KENSUKE] I mean, if I hadn't
dragged him into this...

199
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:28,291
[elevetor doors hum]

200
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:29,750
[gasps]

201
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:34,583
[grunts]

202
00:12:37,708 --> 00:12:39,041
[sighs]

203
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:51,375
Hey. Where's Boss-man?

204
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:55,083
[INOUE]
Does it really matter?

205
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:58,750
[KENSUKE] Have you gotten
in touch with him?

206
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:01,125
Why even ask me that?

207
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:03,125
Because I...

208
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:08,958
[grunts]

209
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:15,375
Fine, then. I'll go.

210
00:13:23,958 --> 00:13:25,625
[grunts]

211
00:13:26,958 --> 00:13:30,333
[grunts, groans]

212
00:13:30,416 --> 00:13:31,333
Kobayashi!

213
00:13:31,416 --> 00:13:32,583
[gasps]

214
00:13:32,666 --> 00:13:33,916
[INOUE]
What's wrong?

215
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,958
[YOSHIO]
My head is all mixed up.

216
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:38,750
Your head?

217
00:13:45,875 --> 00:13:50,916
[YOSHIO whimpers]

218
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:54,666
[screams]

219
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,166
[gasps]

220
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:59,333
[screaming continues]

221
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:03,125
[grunts]

222
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:13,041
[YOSHIO gasps]

223
00:14:16,375 --> 00:14:18,833
[YOSHIO'S DAD grunts]

224
00:14:18,916 --> 00:14:20,666
[YOSHIO'S DAD gasps]

225
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,333
--[YOSHIO'S DAD grunts]
--[YOSHIO groans]

226
00:14:26,416 --> 00:14:31,375
[YOSHIO whimpers]

227
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:39,416
[INOUE]
A Ferris wheel.

228
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:42,875
An amusement park surrounded
by a housing complex.

229
00:14:42,958 --> 00:14:48,125
A park with an octopus slide,
and a train with green lines.

230
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:00,625
[INOUE]
One matches.

231
00:15:00,708 --> 00:15:03,750
It's most likely Akebono
Amusement Park.

232
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:16,041
Well, Kobayashi? Make a choice.
What do you want to do?

233
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:23,833
[NORO grunts]

234
00:15:23,916 --> 00:15:27,375
[YOSHIO grunts]

235
00:15:27,458 --> 00:15:29,500
[INOUE]
Hey! Where are you going?

236
00:15:29,583 --> 00:15:31,250
[YOSHIO]
That amusement park.

237
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:32,250
[KENSUKE gasps]

238
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:34,125
You can't!
You still need to rest!

239
00:15:34,208 --> 00:15:37,125
I have to get rid
of this feeling!

240
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:40,666
[INOUE] What do you
expect to find there?

241
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,166
[gasps]

242
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:49,458
[YOSHIO grunts]
Huh?

243
00:15:54,083 --> 00:15:55,041
[KENSUKE grunts]

244
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:05,583
[grunts]

245
00:16:26,833 --> 00:16:28,958
[NORO]
Hey. Open it.

246
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:29,916
[INOUE]
Hm?

247
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,250
[NORO]
Open the window! Now!

248
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:34,750
What for?

249
00:16:34,833 --> 00:16:37,875
Do it! Or I'll bust my way out!

250
00:16:37,958 --> 00:16:43,125
Pippo! Unleash your
"One-Hundred Pecks of Fury!"

251
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:47,833
[PIPPO hoots]

252
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:49,500
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

253
00:16:53,916 --> 00:16:55,708
Noro?

254
00:16:55,791 --> 00:17:00,208
[PIPPO hoots]

255
00:17:00,291 --> 00:17:02,250
[gasps]

256
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:08,083
[NORO]
Pippo!

257
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:11,583
[KENSUKE gasps]

258
00:17:11,666 --> 00:17:12,791
[NORO]
Attack!

259
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:17,500
--[PIPPO hoots]
--[KENSUKE grunts] Stop it!

260
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:19,458
[NORO]
Stop!

261
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,666
[NORO]
Pippo...

262
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:25,291
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

263
00:17:25,375 --> 00:17:27,333
Tornado!

264
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:29,333
[KENSUKE]
Ah! Stop it! Cut it out!

265
00:17:29,416 --> 00:17:31,125
[NORO]
Stop!

266
00:17:37,041 --> 00:17:39,000
[NORO]
Pippo...

267
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:40,458
--[PIPPO hoots]
--[KENSUKE] Huh?

268
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:43,958
[NORO]
Um... Thunder Snake!

269
00:17:44,041 --> 00:17:48,833
--[PIPPO hoots]
--[KENSUKE screams]

270
00:17:48,916 --> 00:17:49,666
[NORO]
Stop!

271
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:51,500
[KENSUKE gasps]

272
00:17:53,250 --> 00:17:54,708
[NORO]
Pippo...

273
00:17:54,791 --> 00:17:56,583
[KENSUKE growls]
Hey!

274
00:17:56,666 --> 00:18:01,666
[NORO] Um, use "Some Kind
of Awesome Move!"

275
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:05,083
Would you knock it off?
What the hell is this about?

276
00:18:05,166 --> 00:18:07,083
[NORO]
There! Finally!

277
00:18:07,166 --> 00:18:09,208
That's the fire I
was looking for.

278
00:18:09,291 --> 00:18:11,333
Way to go paramecium brain.

279
00:18:11,416 --> 00:18:13,041
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

280
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:15,791
[NORO] Good work, Pippo!
Mission complete.

281
00:18:15,875 --> 00:18:17,791
You can come home now!

282
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:21,125
Huh? Hold on! What gives?

283
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:22,500
I thought you were
going with Inoue

284
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:24,916
to keep an eye on Kobayashi!

285
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:29,041
[NORO] I could. But that's
what you want to do, isn't it?

286
00:18:29,125 --> 00:18:30,583
[KENSUKE gasps]

287
00:18:30,666 --> 00:18:33,250
[NORO] I want to relax with
Pippo and a box of chocolates.

288
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,125
So I'm gonna.

289
00:18:35,208 --> 00:18:36,458
[KENSUKE]
But...

290
00:18:36,541 --> 00:18:38,416
[NORO] Why don't you just
go back to being simple?

291
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:40,416
You kinda suck at being complex.

292
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:41,416
Sad, really.

293
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,458
[KENSUKE growls]

294
00:18:42,541 --> 00:18:44,458
[NORO]
Home, Pippo! Mama's waiting!

295
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:48,500
[PIPPO hoots]

296
00:18:55,208 --> 00:18:56,666
[KENSUKE grunts]

297
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:04,958
[OFFICE WORKERS mutter]

298
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:16,958
[chuckles]

299
00:19:22,458 --> 00:19:23,666
[gasps]

300
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:30,041
[gasps]

301
00:19:30,125 --> 00:19:33,291
[OFFICE WORKERS chatter]

302
00:19:33,375 --> 00:19:35,541
It's nothing.

303
00:19:35,625 --> 00:19:38,708
[OFFICE WORKERS groan]

304
00:19:38,791 --> 00:19:43,250
[gasps]

305
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,708
[gasps]

306
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:58,541
[HIDE, FURUKAWA chuckle]

307
00:20:00,458 --> 00:20:02,000
[phone buzzes]

308
00:20:02,083 --> 00:20:03,500
[HIDE]
Hm?

309
00:20:03,583 --> 00:20:05,041
[gasps]

310
00:20:05,125 --> 00:20:06,833
[HIDE]
Hey, Han! What's up?

311
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:18,416
[HIDE]
Yo! Need a lift?

312
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,666
[KENSUKE]
Yep!

313
00:20:24,666 --> 00:20:26,750
Whoa! Let me slow down!

314
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:30,166
He, he. So, where
are we headed, Han?

315
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:34,333
The Akebono Amusement Park!

316
00:21:08,416 --> 00:21:12,333
[TWENTY-FACES] It's still
not enough, Akechi.

317
00:21:13,583 --> 00:21:14,708
[alarms blaring]

318
00:21:14,791 --> 00:21:17,416
[POLICEMAN A] He's out!
Find and subdue him!

319
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:20,333
If he gets outside,
we'll lose him for good!

320
00:21:26,750 --> 00:21:29,708
[POLICEMAN B]
Stop! Get back to your cell!

321
00:21:29,791 --> 00:21:32,333
[MASKED MAN grunts]

322
00:21:32,416 --> 00:21:34,250
Don't think you
can get out of here!

323
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:35,250
[MASKED MAN]
Outta the way.

324
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:37,166
[POLICEMAN B gasps]

325
00:21:37,250 --> 00:21:38,750
[POLICEMAN B]
Who are you?

326
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:47,458
The Fiend with twenty faces,
of course.

327
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:52,500
♪

328
00:23:40,958 --> 00:23:43,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
"Falling CLown."

